Hlatshwayo was a DJ at Jozi FM for five years and presented a weekend slot. The former Generations and Yizo Yizo actor was shot and killed on Sunday night at a Pub in Pimville, Soweto. The CEO of Jozi FM, Mpho Mhlongo, took to Twitter to confirm his death, who was also a DJ on the local radio station. Police said four men had been taken into custody for questioning in relation to the murder. Hlatshwayo, 40, and his friend Oupa, &#8216;Chom Chom&#8217; Duma were gunned down on Sunday evening when they tried to stop two women from being robbed of their cellphones. The robbers turned on them and shot both of them. They were declared dead on the scene. A portrait of Jozi FM DJ Mandla Hlatshwayo is pictured during a memorial service held in Soweto, 18 May 2017. Picture: Refilwe Modise Murdered Jozi FM dj Mandla Hlatshwayo's girlfriend Mami Maleme, centre, is pictured during a memorial service held in Soweto, 18 May 2017. Picture: Refilwe Modise Mourners celebrate the life of murdered Jozi FM DJ Mandla Hlatshwayo during a memorial service held in his honor held in Soweto, 18 May 2017. Picture: Refilwe Modise A portrait of Jozi FM DJ Mandla Hlatshwayo is pictured during a memorial service held in Soweto, 18 May 2017. Picture: Refilwe Modise A portrait of Jozi FM DJ Mandla Hlatshwayo is pictured during a memorial service held in Soweto, 18 May 2017. Picture: Refilwe Modise Murdered Jozi FM dj Mandla Hlatshwayo's girlfriend Mami Maleme, centre, is pictured during a memorial service held in Soweto, 18 May 2017. Picture: Refilwe Modise Murdered Jozi FM dj Mandla Hlatshwayo's girlfriend Mami Maleme is pictured during a memorial service held in Soweto, 18 May 2017. Picture: Refilwe Modise A portrait of Jozi FM DJ Mandla Hlatshwayo is pictured during a memorial service held in Soweto, 18 May 2017. Picture: Refilwe Modise READ MORE: WATCH: Mandla Hlatshwayo&#8217;s final happy moments captured at Jozi FM studio For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.